    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the way The Self employed income support grants are calculated",
        "additional_details": "The self employed have been left in dreadful financial situations as a result of flawed unfair calculations of their average income. If you have filed trading profits for a whole year\u2019s worth of Self-employment it works well. But as it stands anyone who has filed a tax year which was not a full year is being unfairly penalised. As it brings the average Monthly income down dramatically meaning the grant is no where near 80% the Chancellor\u2019s office states we are entitled to.",
        "background": "Only include full years Of Self-employment and those that actually contain trading profits in the years in calculated.",
